      • add

        void add(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method calls the addEmployee function to add Employee. Before being added, validity on name length, date, hourlyRate and annualSalary is checked.
        Parameters:
        event - on the event of selecting a the addEmployee Button to potentially add Employee.

      • addEmployee

        This method calls the add function in the Company class to add the Employee.
        Parameters:
        employee - employee to be added

      • clear

        Parameters:
        event - on the event of selecting the clearButton, TeaxtArea is cleared.

      • compute

        void compute(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method computes payment for Employees. The method calls the processPayments function which computes Employee payments.
        Parameters:
        event - upon selecting the compute menuItem, Employees payments are computed.

      • disableEmployeeType

        void disableEmployeeType(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)

        Parameters:
        event - on the event of selecting a radioButton, textField and Button

      • enterAllInfoMsg

      • exportFile

        void exportFile(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method exports a textFile. The textFile includes Employee name, department,date, employeeType, hourlyRate and Hours Worked.
        Parameters:
        event - on the event of selecting the export menuItem, the textFile is exported.

      • importFile

        void importFile(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
        This method takes in a ImportFile . The ImportFile will call the function addEmployee and will add the Employees listed in the ImportFile.
        Parameters:
        event - on the event of selecting the import menuItem, the choose textFile will be imported.

      • setHours
